name: Martin Stranka - Into you
description: *Please note to pay by debit/credit card please select the don't have paypal at the paypal payment screen* Martin Stranka - Into you - Edition of 25 (of each print size) 5 sizes available for purchase. Archival museum fiber-based photo paper, Museo Silver rag. Prints last in display conditions without fading for up to 200 years. Each print comes complete with a certificate of authenticity, and each piece is numbered, titled and has the artists signature on the reverse. **Larger sizes may be available upon request, please contact us to discuss your needs further** Martin Stranka LtDedition is delighted to bring to you the incredible work of the Internationally award winning photographer, Martin Stranka. Martin is a self-taught professional photographer, born in the Czech Republic. Martins`s distinctive vision of photography is etched as a unique space located in a balance and serenity, while his sophisticated and rewarding images exist in that narrow window of a few seconds between dreaming and awakening. During the last three years Martin has won over 40 major international photography awards from different competitions, including Professional Photographer of the Year, Emerging Talent Award (in the Nikon International Photo Contest), Sony World Photography Awards, EISA Photo Maestro and International Photo Awards two years in a row. His solo and group exhibitions have been seen from South and North America, through Europe, all the way to Asia. His photographs have been exhibited in places such as New York, Los Angeles, Tokyo, Milan, London, Miami, Paris, Dubai, Germany, Prague, Brussels, North Carolina, Hong Kong, Ukraine, Vienna and many more. Martins`s work has been showcased in prestigious galleries such as Getty Images Gallery, Saatchi Gallery and Robert Fontaine Gallery. His work stood proudly alongside the likes of Andy Warhol, Annie Leibovitz, Banksy, Damien Hirst, Helmut Newton, Albert Watson and Roxanne Lowit.

name: Raul Egido Val - Cyber Girl V6
description: *Please note to pay by debit/credit card please select the don't have paypal at the paypal payment screen* Raul Egido Val - Cyber Girl V6 - 1/1 Original Size - A4 (29.7cm x 21.0 cm). An original piece of work by the Spanish artist Raul Egido Val produced using Acrylic, spraypaint and indian ink on paper. Due to the nature of these pieces, all originals by this artist come mounted "passepartout". This original will be shipped flat, and is ready to be framed, or can be purchased pre-framed for a small additional cost. **Please select the "Pre-framed" option if you wish to purchase the print framed (example picture shown). This is at a cost of GBP50 with no additional postage to pay above the standard rates** Raul Egido Val LtDedition is delighted to bring to you a number of original examples from the Spanish artist Raul Egido Val. Hailing from Zaragoza in Northern Spain, since early age Egido discovered arts and began drawing strange and complex machines which impressed his teachers and others alike, a “surreal and fantastic sci fi” approach to visual imaginery which he still uses in his work today. At age 6 he visited the Dalí museum in Figueres where he was exposed for the first time to the work of the master surrealist himself. This visit played an important role in the development of his artistic side and own pyschology. Computers and graphic design were next, a connection which helped him to develop an early interest in machines, techonolgy and electronics, which can be seen widely across his work today. Cinema, comics and Science fiction also made a big impact on him. Reminiscences of some of his dancing years can be seen in the movement and fluidity of his works. It wasn´t until 2009 where at the age of 22, he decided to quit the art school in order to focus on his own personal and original artistic approach and began his artistic career as an "outsider" in an area not known for for his style of art. Since then Egido has been developing his own visual style through different techniques, mainly drawing and painting, creating the base in which he stands now and preparing him for all the new challenges to come and reaching a far wider audience that he has up until now. His own way of understanding the visual language helped him win some important prizes, although he´s been remaining underground in order to create a strong and original character. After a long journey of intense work and self-awareness along with progression in his own style, Egido has been putting all the pieces together, he is now prepared to showcase his talents to a worldwide audience with his own and very distinctive style. Althought his art has many different influences Egido likes to use term “CYBEREXPRESSIONISM” Which he describes as the only possible art answer to the world we live in."
